AnalyzeCopy - black box validation suite for copying files


==== INSTALL ====

In order to run AnalyzeCopy you must install:

 1. Ruby

 2. Rake, http://rake.rubyforge.org/
    can usually be installed by with this command: gem install --remote rake

 3. Python

 4. Perl

 5. osxutils (version 1.7), http://osxutils.sourceforge.net/

 6. xbup (version 2.0), http://www.shoup.net/xbup/
    installation procedure for xbup can be found on page 6 in it's doc.pdf.
    if you just do a make, make install, then it will install itself in ~/bin

 7. sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install File::Copy::Recursive'



Now compile AnalyzeCopy:

prompt> cd utils
prompt> pwd
/Users/johndoe/code/AnalyzeCopy/utils
prompt> rake
prompt>

AnalyzeCopy is now ready to be used.


==== USING ANALYZECOPY ====

prompt> pwd
/Users/johndoe/code/AnalyzeCopy
prompt> rake
prompt>

You will be prompted for "sudo" password, since some
of the tests requires root.


